<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-02-14T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-02-14T17:00:00-05:00" n="16" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d16">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">863.00/862a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi></persName>)<note n="11" xml:id="d16fn11">The same telegram was sent, <hi rend="italic">mutatis mutandis</hi>, on February 14, 5 p.m.,
                                    to the Ambassadors in France and Italy.</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-14T17:00:00-05:00">February 14, 1934—5
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Please telegraph a brief analysis of reaction in Great Britain to
                                recent developments in the Austrian situation.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>